# Design tokens

**Source of truth:** [design/tokens.json](../../design/tokens.json) — not hand-edited generated files.

## Workflow

1. Edit `design/tokens.json`
2. Run `cd web && npm run tokens:generate` (or `node scripts/generate-design-tokens.mjs`)
3. Commit generated outputs: `web/src/styles/tokens.generated.css`, iOS `Colors.xcassets`, `Theme.swift`, `TtfTier.swift`, `web/src/lib/ttfTier.ts`, `web/src/lib/mapPin.ts`

## Visual design docs

- Kit (voice, mocks, reference components): [docs/design-system/readme.md](../../docs/design-system/readme.md)
- Token reference: [docs/DESIGN_TOKENS.md](../../docs/DESIGN_TOKENS.md)
- Map basemap: [docs/MAP_STYLE.md](../../docs/MAP_STYLE.md)
- Live QA: [docs/TEST_FLOWS.md](../../docs/TEST_FLOWS.md)

Kit CSS under `docs/design-system/tokens/` uses `--ls-*` names for HTML mocks only. Production uses generated Tailwind `@theme` vars.

## Code rules

- Web: use semantic Tailwind classes (`bg-brand`, `text-text-muted`, `font-display`) — not raw hex in components
- iOS: use `Color.brand`, `Color.text`, `Color.ttfFast`, etc. from generated Theme — not `.primary` / hardcoded hex
- ScoutLogo and map pin fallbacks should use CSS vars or generated constants
